cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a game-theoretic framework for modeling the interaction among self-interested consumers in a smart grid. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves optimization and machine learning techniques to determine optimal nonstationary DSM strategies, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with cybersecurity issues related to incentive-compatible strategies, which could place it in cs.CYBER (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of DSM on billing and discomfort costs, which could make it relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
